TTYCHATTER-GEMINI-NCURSES-PYTHON(1)          User Commands          TTYCHATTER-GEMINI-NCURSES-PYTHON(1)

NAME
    ttychatter-gemini-ncurses-python - Python ncurses terminal chat client for Gemini

SYNOPSIS
    ttychatter-gemini-ncurses-python
    ttychatter-gemini-ncurses-python <session_name>
    ttychatter-gemini-ncurses-python --resume <session_name>
    ttychatter-gemini-ncurses-python --list
    ttychatter-gemini-ncurses-python --models
    ttychatter-gemini-ncurses-python --update-models
    ttychatter-gemini-ncurses-python --test-model <model_id>
    ttychatter-gemini-ncurses-python --doctor
    ttychatter-gemini-ncurses-python --version
    ttychatter-gemini-ncurses-python --help

DESCRIPTION
    ttychatter-gemini-ncurses-python is the full-screen Python ncurses implementation of
    ttychatter.  It is the behavioral reference implementation for
    the future native C ncurses client, ttychatter-gemini-ncurses.

    The program is intended for end users who want a robust terminal chat
    client rather than a browser interface or a developer curl example.  It
    provides conversation sessions, model discovery, model testing, file
    attachments, memory snapshots, external editor support, mousewheel
    scrolling, command menus, and diagnostics.

USAGE
    Start a new timestamped chat:

        ttychatter-gemini-ncurses-python

    Start or open a named chat:

        ttychatter-gemini-ncurses-python android-backup

    Resume a named chat:

        ttychatter-gemini-ncurses-python --resume android-backup

    List saved sessions:

        ttychatter-gemini-ncurses-python --list

    List cached models, fetching if cache is missing:

        ttychatter-gemini-ncurses-python --models

    Refresh model cache from Google:

        ttychatter-gemini-ncurses-python --update-models

    Test one model:

        ttychatter-gemini-ncurses-python --test-model gemini-2.5-flash

    Run diagnostics:

        ttychatter-gemini-ncurses-python --doctor

CONTROLS
    F1
        Open actionable help / command menu.

    Ctrl+G
        Send current message.

    F2
        Model menu.  The model menu can use cached models, update the model
        list from Google, select a model, test a highlighted model, view model
        metadata, and save the selected model to config.

    F3
        API-key manager.  Runtime keys are not saved unless the user chooses a
        save action.

    F4
        Session browser.  Opens existing sessions, creates new timestamped
        sessions, and renames the current session.

    F5
        Options menu.  The options screen is a form-like menu for config-backed
        settings rather than a raw config-file editor.

    F6
        Memory menu.  View, edit, clear, or rebuild current conversation
        context.

    F7
        Files and attachments menu.  Attach local files for the next prompt and
        browse saved attachments.

    F8
        External editor menu.  Detects common editors, allows manual editor
        entry, allows browsing for an executable, and opens the current prompt
        in the chosen editor.

    F9
        Credits/about screen.

    F10, Ctrl+Q
        Quit.

    PgUp, PgDn
        Scroll transcript or visible lists.

    Mouse wheel
        Scroll transcript and menus where supported by the terminal emulator.

    Left click
        Select visible menu rows, place input cursor, or activate clickable
        command-strip labels where supported.

GLOBAL NAVIGATION
    Function keys are treated as global navigation where practical.  A user who
    accidentally opens one feature screen should be able to press another
    function key directly instead of first backing out through Esc.  This
    behavior is part of the intended UI contract because it prevents users from
    getting trapped in modal screens.

MODEL DISCOVERY
    Available Gemini models can be listed with:

        ttychatter-gemini-ncurses-python --models

    The model cache can be refreshed with:

        ttychatter-gemini-ncurses-python --update-models

    The underlying Gemini REST command is:

        curl "https://generativelanguage.googleapis.com/v1beta/models?key=YOUR_API_KEY"

    The model selector uses metadata such as supportedGenerationMethods,
    inputTokenLimit, outputTokenLimit, displayName, and description.  The tool
    does not claim to permanently know the best model because Google's model
    list can change.

MODEL TESTING
    Autoscan/probing has been removed.  The program uses user-operated testing:
    select one model, send one configured test prompt, read the raw response,
    then activate or save the model if desired.

CONFIGURATION
    Configuration file:

        ~/.config/ttychatter/gemini/config

    The path still uses ttychatter-gemini-python3 for backward compatibility with older
    releases and with the Bash implementations.

    Supported keys include:

        MODEL
            Gemini model identifier.

        CONTEXT_TURNS
            Recent user/assistant exchanges sent back as conversation context.

        HISTORY_LIMIT
            Legacy alias for CONTEXT_TURNS.

        GEMINI_API_KEY
            Optional API key.  Environment variable takes priority.

        SESSION_DIR
            Session log directory.  Default: ~/.gpt

        ATTACHMENT_DIR
            Attachment/artifact directory.  Default: SESSION_DIR/attachments

        EDITOR
            External editor command.

        MODEL_TEST_PROMPT
            Prompt used by model testing.

        MAX_ATTACHMENT_BYTES
            Maximum local attachment size accepted by the UI.

        MONOCHROME
            Disable reliance on dim/grey styling.

        INPUT_PLACEHOLDER
            Placeholder shown in an empty input box.

        STARTUP_NOTICE
            Enable or disable the temporary Project Lead startup notice.

        MODEL_FILTER_GENERATE_CONTENT
        MODEL_FILTER_REQUIRE_TOKENS
        MODEL_FILTER_HIDE_PREVIEW
        MODEL_MIN_INPUT_TOKENS
        MODEL_MIN_OUTPUT_TOKENS
        MODEL_SORT_ORDER
            Model metadata filter and sorting options.

ENVIRONMENT
    GEMINI_API_KEY
        Preferred API-key source.

    VISUAL, EDITOR
        Used by external editor support if EDITOR is not set in config.

FILES
    ~/.config/ttychatter/gemini/config
        Shared config file.

    SESSION_DIR/*.log
        Human-readable session logs.

    ATTACHMENT_DIR/
        Code block artifacts, local file artifacts, and generated inlineData
        attachments where the model/API returns such data.

MEMORY MODEL
    ttychatter-gemini-ncurses-python keeps rolling conversation context in memory and
    writes memory snapshots into session logs.  When a session is resumed, the
    latest usable memory snapshot is preferred; if none exists, recent chat
    entries are used to rebuild context.

DIAGNOSTICS
    --doctor checks local environment readiness: Python, curses, TERM, terminal
    size, config, API-key presence, session directory, attachment directory,
    model-cache directory, editor availability, and DNS.  It does not print API
    key values and does not call generateContent.

LIMITATIONS
    - Requires Python 3 with curses support.
    - Requires internet access for API calls.
    - Model/media support depends on Gemini model capability and API limits.
    - Mouse support depends on terminal emulator support for ncurses mouse
      events.
    - Terminal text selection and drag-copy remain terminal-emulator features.

VERSION
    ttychatter-gemini-ncurses-python version 0.9.3

AUTHOR
    Part of the ttychatter project.
